# Ycode Documentation Writing Guidelines

## Important: Cloud vs Open Source

Ycode has two versions: **Ycode Cloud** (managed, at ycode.com) and **Ycode Open Source** (self-hosted).
Most features are identical. When writing docs:
- Write feature docs to apply to BOTH versions (editor, CMS, forms, etc.)
- Only call out Cloud vs Open Source differences in setup/deployment pages
- Use Callout boxes to note when a section is Cloud-only or Open Source-only

## Source of Truth

The Ycode product source code is at `/Users/ignas/Sites/opensource/`. When writing documentation, read the relevant source files to ensure accuracy. Key directories:

- `app/ycode/` - Editor routes and components
- `app/ycode/api/` - API routes
- `lib/repositories/` - Data access layer
- `lib/services/` - Business logic
- `stores/` - Zustand state stores
- `types/index.ts` - TypeScript type definitions
- `database/migrations/` - Database schema

## Writing Style

- Write in second person ("you"), present tense
- Be clear and concise, avoid filler words
- Do not use emojis
- Use active voice ("Click Save" not "The Save button should be clicked")
- Keep paragraphs short (2-4 sentences)

## MDX Page Structure

Every page follows this pattern:

```mdx
---
title: Page Title
---

import { Callout } from 'nextra/components'
import { Steps } from 'nextra/components'

# Page Title

Brief intro paragraph (1-2 sentences).

## Section

Content...

<Callout type="info">
  Helpful tip or important note.
</Callout>
```

## Available Components

- `<Callout type="info|warning|error">` - Tips, warnings, errors
- `<Steps>` - Step-by-step instructions (wrap ### headings)
- `<Screenshot src="filename.png" alt="..." caption="..." />` - Screenshots from `public/screenshots/`
- `<Video src="filename.mp4" caption="..." />` - Screen recordings from `public/videos/`
- `<KeyboardShortcut keys="Cmd+S" />` - Keyboard shortcut badges
- `<FeatureCard>` / `<FeatureGrid>` - Feature overview cards
- `<Tabs>` / `<Tab>` from `nextra/components` - Tabbed content

## Folder Index Pages

For folders with child pages, use `asIndexPage: true`:

```mdx
---
title: Section Name
asIndexPage: true
---
```

Do NOT add the folder's `index` key in its `_meta.ts` when using `asIndexPage: true`.

